INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18187, 61, 10, 9.00, '2024-01-15', 'expert_overall', 'I love playing in the Adidas AE 1. The traction is outstanding, the cushioning feels comfortable, and the support and lockdown keep you secure.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18188, 61, 9, 9.00, '2024-03-22', 'expert_overall', 'The Adidas AE 1 is in the running for best performer of the year. I love the traction and cushioning setup. This shoe is one of my favourite performance models.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18189, 61, 7, 8.90, '2023-12-28', 'expert_overall', 'The Adidas AE 1 has outstanding performance. The support and cushioning are some of the best; the only downside is the weight.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18190, 61, 5, 8.80, '2024-01-15', 'expert_overall', 'The Adidas AE 1 feels complete. I feel ready to play in this shoe. The cushioning is elite, and the traction holds up as well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18191, 61, 111, 8.80, '2024-01-02', 'expert_overall', 'The Adidas AE 1 is a dope performer. It''s sturdy and well-built. It has the traction, cushioning, and support that players need.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18192, 61, 3, 8.60, '2023-12-28', 'expert_overall', 'I''m loving the Adidas AE 1. The step-in cushioning feels comfortable, and the lockdown is impressive. My only gripes are the weight and breathability.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18193, 61, 99, 8.60, '2024-01-11', 'expert_overall', 'The standout features of the Adidas AE 1 are the stability and cushioning. This is one of the best performance shoes if you enjoy the materials.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18194, 61, 2, 8.60, '2024-02-18', 'expert_overall', 'I like the direction Adidas is going with the AE 1. The cushioning feels good, the traction is grippy, and I felt secure in these shoes.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18195, 61, 19, 8.60, '2024-05-01', 'expert_overall', 'The Adidas AE 1 debuts with a solid score for performance. Lateral stability is the only downside. The traction is perfect, and the cushioning feels comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18196, 61, 1, 8.40, '2023-12-28', 'expert_overall', 'The Adidas AE 1 is an easy shoe to play in. It feels buttery underfoot despite being heavy. The foam choices for the cushioning are incredible.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18197, 61, 6, 8.20, '2024-01-11', 'expert_overall', 'I have no problem recommending the Adidas AE 1 at this price point. The traction is phenomenal, but I did experience some sliding on the footbed.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18198, 61, 145, 8.80, '2024-01-17', 'user_overall', 'The traction is exceptional. So is the cushion of this shoe . Its really comfortable , budget shoe and I love the looks . The only disadvantages are that this shoe is heavy (but I dont mind it that much ) and it is not that breathable . Also the laces gets untied easily(maybe its my fault). Overall this shoe is amazing and I would recommend it for powerful guards and wings .They are really similar to the hardens that I have played in but I might choose the ae over them.Ineedmoretimetryingthem');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18199, 61, 146, 8.80, '2024-05-12', 'user_overall', 'Overall the Adidas AE1 is a top performer and I find out performs most shoes that Ive tried (Harden 7, Ja 1, etc). The durability of the shoe after a playing a few tournaments was excellent, however I did notice some scuffing on the rubber sidewalls of the shoe, You cant see the scuffs from far but are noticeable when you have the shoe in hand. Traction on them is one of the best Ive tried, but if you play on dusty courts the space in between the ridges gets really dusty. Overall great shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18200, 61, 93, 8.80, '2025-07-17', 'user_overall', 'Traction is pretty grippy and bites well, does pick up a little bit of dust but just wipe and youll be fine. Cushion is really nice in the heel and comfy, I wish the forefoot used boost as well but good impact protection, comfy, and bouncy. Materials are soft and supportive and pretty well paded, only downside is that theyre so heavy. Its a high top so it supportive and the laces lock you in well, never felt unstable. Sometimes it can be a little tricky to get on being a high top,butfitsnice.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18201, 61, 74, 9.00, '2024-05-09', 'user_overall', 'traction is top tier and bites very hard (dust doesnt effect it either). cushion is very comfy but only missed 10 because impact protection could be better but you sacrifice that for court feel. X plate feels similar to gt cut 3 but with more torsion support. tpu side walls are very supportive, amazing, but missed on 10 on materials because there so heavy combined with the amount of rubber on shoe. prolonged play can make your feet feel really hot for lack of ventilation. overall top tier shoe!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18202, 61, 147, 9.60, '2024-10-26', 'user_overall', 'This shoe was beautiful from the day it released. Since I havent had really good experiences with adidas since the harden vol 7, i thought the colorways were the only good thing about it. But i was definitely wrong. This shoe from the traction to cushion to the material were amazing. It is also wide-foot friendly and It fits likes a glove so I would say go true to size. One of my favorite players right now and i hope to see more good adidas shoes like this one. One negative really is the laces.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18203, 61, 10, 10.00, '2024-01-15', 'traction', 'The traction is outstanding. You stop on a dime and instantaneously. It performs exceptionally on dusty courts, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18204, 61, 9, 10.00, '2024-03-22', 'traction', 'The traction has minimal dust pickup and impressive performance. The pattern grips insanely well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18205, 61, 7, 9.00, '2023-12-28', 'traction', 'The traction performs on all surfaces as long as you occasionally wipe off the dust.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18206, 61, 5, 9.00, '2024-01-15', 'traction', 'I enjoy the traction performance. I didn''t have any problems.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18207, 61, 111, 9.00, '2024-01-02', 'traction', 'I love the traction. It''s a top-tier performer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18208, 61, 3, 8.00, '2023-12-28', 'traction', 'The traction performance is decent. It stops well but loses its magic on dusty courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18209, 61, 99, 9.00, '2024-01-11', 'traction', 'The traction performance is great, but it takes time to warm up.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18210, 61, 2, 9.00, '2024-02-18', 'traction', 'The traction is grippy on clean indoor courts. The only downside is the dust pickup.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18211, 61, 19, 10.00, '2024-05-01', 'traction', 'The groove thickness, outsole pattern, and rubber rigidity provide perfect traction performance.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18212, 61, 1, 8.00, '2023-12-28', 'traction', 'The outsole is the most well-engineered part of the shoe. It does well on all surfaces, but it''s better for stronger players because of the weight.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18213, 61, 6, 10.00, '2024-01-11', 'traction', 'The traction on this shoe is phenomenal. It performs on clean and dusty courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18214, 61, 10, 9.00, '2024-01-15', 'cushion', 'The shank provides a springy feeling on propulsion. I enjoyed the cushioning setup. It feels fantastic, even better than the Harden 7.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18215, 61, 9, 9.00, '2024-03-22', 'cushion', 'The cushioning feels amazing. It''s one of the best setups available. I felt incredibly comfortable during play. Impact protection could be better for bigger players.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18216, 61, 7, 9.50, '2023-12-28', 'cushion', 'I enjoy the plush cushioning setup. The Boost is under the heel, and the forefoot is Lightstrike. It covers all my needs, and I consider it the best setup on the market.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18217, 61, 5, 10.00, '2024-01-15', 'cushion', 'The cushioning stands out immediately. This is one of the best setups available. It has impact protection and responsiveness.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18218, 61, 111, 9.00, '2024-01-02', 'cushion', 'The cushioning is one of my favourite features. It feels incredible on my feet. It has responsiveness and impact protection.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18219, 61, 3, 9.00, '2023-12-28', 'cushion', 'The step-in comfort feels incredible, and the performance is pretty good. It''s responsive with a subtle bounce.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18220, 61, 99, 9.00, '2024-01-11', 'cushion', 'The cushioning is comfortable and stable. It''s springy and responsive. I especially like how the shoe handles impact protection.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18221, 61, 2, 8.00, '2024-02-18', 'cushion', 'The Jetboost and Lightstrike feel better than the standard Boost. It''s a solid improvement in cushioning for an Adidas shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18222, 61, 19, 9.00, '2024-05-01', 'cushion', 'The impact protection feels solid in the heel and forefoot. The midsole feels comfortable during explosive movements.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18223, 61, 1, 9.00, '2023-12-28', 'cushion', 'The shoe is bottom-heavy because of the thick Boost and the substantial shanks. The energy return is even between shock absorption and bounciness.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18224, 61, 6, 8.00, '2024-01-11', 'cushion', 'The forefoot feels low to the ground. There''s not much compression. This setup caters to shifty players.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18225, 61, 10, 8.00, '2024-01-15', 'materials', 'The upper is hefty, but I like the quality of the textile materials. My only complaint is the shoe scuffs easily.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18226, 61, 9, 8.00, '2024-03-22', 'materials', 'The materials are supportive and feel secure. The combination of different materials feels comfortable as well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18227, 61, 7, 8.00, '2023-12-28', 'materials', 'The textile collar doesn''t offer much, but the rubber side walls perform well. The main downside is the weight of the shoe. It''s on the heavy side.');
