INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18740, 72, 3, 8.20, '2023-12-06', 'expert_overall', 'The Li-Ning Wade Shadow 5 is a decent performer, especially for a budget shoe. Stability is the best feature, while traction and cushion take some time to warm up.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18741, 72, 10, 8.00, '2024-01-15', 'expert_overall', 'I like the Li-Ning Wade Shadow 5 as a budget performer. The shoe is impressive for lockdown, and the traction and cushioning are decent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18742, 72, 1, 7.80, '2023-12-06', 'expert_overall', 'The Li-Ning Wade Shadow 5 is better for outdoor use. The shoe caters to larger, more powerful players that can generate more force for traction and cushioning.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18743, 72, 180, 7.50, '2024-08-08', 'user_overall', 'I take mia regular size but my feet cant enter in the shoes of the boom''s insoles are in them. I have t remove them and play without Any insoles. Those shoes is very tight. The worst part Is that After One outdoor game, the rubber of the traction start t brake. Seriosly...Pieces of Rubber start cut and now After One week the traction Is flat and with a lot of scuffs...');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18744, 72, 181, 9.20, '2024-03-28', 'user_overall', 'Traction was great, shoes were comfortable to wear even though it took a few games to break in. Feels good outdoors and even better indoors. Got a discount but I think it would still be worth full price. Great option for courts where traction can be a problem.');
