INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18901, 76, 7, 8.90, '2023-11-08', 'expert_overall', 'The Under Armour Curry 11 is Steph Curry''s best signature model. I enjoyed the updated cushioning. The fit and support are stellar, and the traction is fantastic.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18902, 76, 103, 8.80, '2023-12-28', 'expert_overall', 'I love the Curry 11 more than the Curry 10. The traction is elite, and the cushioning caters to shooters nicely. It uses the best iteration of Flow, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18903, 76, 111, 8.80, '2023-11-08', 'expert_overall', 'The Under Armour Curry 11 is the perfect guard shoe. It has you covered in all directions and through all movements.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18904, 76, 3, 8.60, '2023-10-23', 'expert_overall', 'The Under Armour Curry 11 keeps all the best performance features of the Curry 10. It''s a fantastic shoe with excellent traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18905, 76, 10, 8.60, '2023-11-08', 'expert_overall', 'The Curry 11 is more of the same. The traction continues to be impressive, and the cushion is low to the ground and responsive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18906, 76, 1, 8.40, '2023-10-28', 'expert_overall', 'The Curry 11 is an improvement from previous models. I love the Flow foam setup, the weight, and the traction. It''s more laterally stable as well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18907, 76, 192, 9.70, '2024-03-16', 'user_overall', 'I''m a big martial arts fan, which was why I had to get a pair of Bruce Lee Fire Curry 11s for my 19th birthday. The red and yellow is amazing. I love the holographic Curry logo spliced with the Yin and Yang on the tongue of the shoe. I haven''t tried these on the court yet but I''m sure I''ll love these as I am familiar of how Under Armour''s new lineup of sneakers with Flow will perform. The only downside is the weird sizing. It may just dethrone my 4 Flotro as my favorite pair of Currys one day.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18908, 76, 193, 8.00, '2024-05-12', 'user_overall', 'The Curry 11 delivers exceptional performance, combining lightweight construction with responsive cushioning for agile movement on the court. Its grippy outsole provides excellent traction, enhancing stability during quick cuts and pivots. The sleek design and supportive fit make it a top choice for basketball players seeking speed and control.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18909, 76, 106, 9.30, '2025-01-15', 'user_overall', 'i love the traction, it help me change direction and make cuts. the cushioning is increadible,super soft and protect my feet from impact. But dont play this shoes outdoor because the outsole is flow foam and does not contain any rubber');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18910, 76, 194, 9.00, '2024-01-09', 'user_overall', 'i like the cushion, materials support and traction on clean courts. the traction was not very good on dust but one wit wo');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18911, 76, 195, 6.70, '2023-12-29', 'user_overall', 'Don''t buy these shoes! The track is absolutely horrible on dusty courts and the shoe tears down after a few weeks of play.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18912, 76, 7, 9.00, '2023-11-08', 'traction', 'The outsole feels tackier than the last model. Dust pickup is not an issue, which is an improvement.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18913, 76, 103, 9.00, '2023-12-28', 'traction', 'The traction is killer on clean courts. It performs well on slightly dusty courts, too. Just avoid playing on courts with extreme levels of dust.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18914, 76, 111, 10.00, '2023-11-08', 'traction', 'Flow continues to be the best traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18915, 76, 3, 9.00, '2023-10-23', 'traction', 'The traction performance is what you expect from Flow foam.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18916, 76, 10, 10.00, '2023-11-08', 'traction', 'Flow foam is an outstanding traction setup. If it ain''t broke, don''t fix it.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18917, 76, 1, 9.00, '2023-10-28', 'traction', 'The outsole feels tackier than the Curry 9 and 10. The grip does not budge.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18918, 76, 7, 9.00, '2023-11-08', 'cushion', 'The dual-density foam feels more comfortable. The impact protection is improved, especially under the heel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18919, 76, 103, 9.00, '2023-12-28', 'cushion', 'The dual-density Flow setup caters to players who enjoy stability and responsiveness. This iteration of Flow is the best for versatility.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18920, 76, 111, 8.00, '2023-11-08', 'cushion', 'The cushioning setup is improved. The impact protection feels better.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18921, 76, 3, 9.00, '2023-10-23', 'cushion', 'The cushioning is dual-density Flow, but it feels the same under feet. The transition is fluent, which is a highlight.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18922, 76, 10, 8.00, '2023-11-08', 'cushion', 'The cushioning is how I expect Flow to feel. It''s comfortable, but the main focus is on responsiveness.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18923, 76, 1, 9.00, '2023-10-28', 'cushion', 'The shank setup is different this year, which I like. There are also two layers of Flow foam. The foam feels bouncier under the forefoot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18924, 76, 7, 8.00, '2023-11-08', 'materials', 'The materials house your foot within the shoe nicely. I enjoyed the materials, even if they don''t feel premium.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18925, 76, 103, 8.00, '2023-12-28', 'materials', 'The Warp and knit materials provide flexibility and breathability. I enjoy the materials.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18926, 76, 111, 9.00, '2023-11-08', 'materials', 'It''s a light sneaker that feels good on foot. The shoe is breathable, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18927, 76, 3, 9.00, '2023-10-23', 'materials', 'I''m happy with the upper materials. This Curry model has the best materials of the latest models.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18928, 76, 10, 9.00, '2023-11-08', 'materials', 'The upper is thin and minimal while remaining structured. I like how the upper feels.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18929, 76, 1, 8.00, '2023-10-28', 'materials', 'I like the containment of the upper. It feels supportive and comfortable. The only thing to worry about is breathability.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18930, 76, 7, 9.50, '2023-11-08', 'support', 'I have to commend Under Armour for how supportive the Curry lineup is. The shoe is incredibly stable and secure.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18931, 76, 103, 9.00, '2023-12-28', 'support', 'My feet weren''t shifting anywhere. Heel, midfoot, and forefoot lockdown felt great.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18932, 76, 111, 8.00, '2023-11-08', 'support', 'I never had any heel slippage issues.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18933, 76, 3, 8.00, '2023-10-23', 'support', 'There''s no heel slippage, and the lockdown is decent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18934, 76, 10, 8.00, '2023-11-08', 'support', 'I felt good with the lateral containment. I didn''t have issues with stability or ankle support, either.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18935, 76, 1, 8.00, '2023-10-28', 'support', 'Containment is impressive. The shoe is better suited for ankle sprains.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18936, 76, 7, 9.00, '2023-11-08', 'fit', 'The fit is snug. There''s no movement inside the shoe. I have no complaints.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18937, 76, 103, 9.00, '2023-12-28', 'fit', 'The fit is one of my favourite parts of the shoe. This shoe fits me extremely well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18938, 76, 3, 8.00, '2023-10-23', 'fit', 'The fit is tight and snug.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18939, 76, 10, 8.00, '2023-11-08', 'fit', 'The shoe fits well, and the materials stretch to accommodate your foot nicely.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18940, 76, 1, 8.00, '2023-10-28', 'fit', 'The materials are more forgiving while still being supportive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18941, 76, 7, 0.00, '2023-11-08', 'outdoor', 'I wouldn''t take this shoe outdoors.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18942, 76, 10, 50.00, '2023-11-08', 'outdoor', 'Outdoor play is adequate.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18943, 76, 1, 0.00, '2023-10-28', 'outdoor', 'This shoe is not meant for outdoor courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18944, 76, 1, 3.00, '2023-10-28', 'width', '2E feet can go true to size for a performance fit (requires a long break-in period) or up half a size for a roomier fit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18945, 76, 3, 2.00, '2023-10-23', 'size', 'It''s safer to go half a size up.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18946, 76, 10, 2.00, '2023-11-08', 'size', 'I went up half a size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18947, 76, 1, 3.00, '2023-10-28', 'size', 'Narrow and medium feet can go true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18948, 77, 7, 9.00, '2023-09-11', 'expert_overall', 'The Air Jordan 38 is a fantastic basketball shoe. The cushioning, materials, and support are all improved. This is the best Jordan Brand shoe in a while.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18949, 77, 111, 8.80, '2023-09-09', 'expert_overall', 'I recommend the Jordan 38 to everyone. I love the bouncy Zoom Strobel and the top-tier traction. My only gripe is the poor toe box materials.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18950, 77, 2, 8.80, '2023-09-18', 'expert_overall', 'The Air Jordan 38 is an improvement compared to the last model. The cushioning, stability, and materials are all better. I enjoyed the zero break-in time.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18951, 77, 3, 8.60, '2023-09-03', 'expert_overall', 'The Air Jordan 38 is well worth the price. The traction and cushioning feel great. Jordan Brand paid attention to the details to make this shoe a top performer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18952, 77, 99, 8.60, '2023-09-16', 'expert_overall', 'I enjoyed playing in the Air Jordan 38. The traction performed well on all courts, and the cushioning is some of Jordan''s best. My outsole did separate, which was disappointing.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18953, 77, 10, 8.40, '2023-08-30', 'expert_overall', 'The Air Jordan 38 is responsive and comfortable. The traction performs on clean courts, and the support is solid. I prefer the cushioning setup with bounce and comfort, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18954, 77, 1, 8.20, '2023-08-12', 'expert_overall', 'The Air Jordan 38 is a perfect containing and maximalist shoe. The support and lockdown are improved, and the cushioning is comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18955, 77, 196, 9.20, '2023-09-26', 'user_overall', 'Great shoe. I think its worth the price. My last model of these were the 35s. Definitely a noticeable improvement in all areas. Almost no break-in.Feel very comfortable and provide tons of support and impact protection. Currently, my go-to shoe to play. Best try them in store but I feel they will accommodate some slight wide footers like me. Didn''t have to go half size but went true to size and feels great but best try them in store to be safe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18956, 77, 197, 8.20, '2024-03-16', 'user_overall', 'Shoes cushion was noisy and right shoe sank more than the left. My wife noticed this too. Left shoes toe box was a little narrow for me, otherwise f');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18957, 77, 131, 9.40, '2024-02-22', 'user_overall', 'Shoe of the year in my opinion also these look incredible. Highly recommend them cushion, traction and support are all incredible features of this shoe. Just don''t take em outside. Also, these are super good for ventilation too. AND the low top version is also amazing these are just amazing.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18958, 77, 198, 9.30, '2025-02-18', 'user_overall', 'Really good hoop shoes, amazing traction but its picks dust on really Dusty courts, cushion amazing walking on clouds, it supports your foot pretty good and the durability is ok, I had a little bit off the outsolle ripping off but its doesn t affect playing much');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18959, 77, 199, 9.10, '2024-12-14', 'user_overall', 'Great cushioning and stability. The shoe fits any style of play. The traction is sneaky good however I had a piece of it rip of only a few weeks of use.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18960, 77, 7, 8.50, '2023-09-11', 'traction', 'The traction is outstanding on clean courts. You''ll have to wipe every 4 or 5 plays on dirty courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18961, 77, 111, 9.00, '2023-09-09', 'traction', 'The traction is top-tier. I stopped on a dime.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18962, 77, 2, 8.00, '2023-09-18', 'traction', 'The traction grips well indoors.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18963, 77, 3, 9.00, '2023-09-03', 'traction', 'You can''t go wrong with herringbone. Dust pickup didn''t affect the grip, either.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18964, 77, 99, 9.00, '2023-09-16', 'traction', 'The traction performed well on all the courts I played on. It''s tacky and grippy, and it handles dust well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18965, 77, 10, 8.00, '2023-08-30', 'traction', 'On clean courts, the traction feels very good. My experience on dust was less than stellar.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18966, 77, 1, 8.00, '2023-08-12', 'traction', 'The best part of the traction is the flanges on the lateral side. It helps with pivoting. The grip is elite when new.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18967, 77, 7, 9.00, '2023-09-11', 'cushion', 'The full-length Zoom Strobel is an upgrade compared to last year. It''s springy and comfortable underfoot. The Cushlon 3.0 is soft, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18968, 77, 111, 10.00, '2023-09-09', 'cushion', 'Cushioning is my favourite part. The Cushlon is soft, and I love the Zoom Strobel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18969, 77, 2, 10.00, '2023-09-18', 'cushion', 'The full-length Zoom Strobel cushioning is one of the best available. It feels bouncy and responsive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18970, 77, 3, 10.00, '2023-09-03', 'cushion', 'The midsole is consistently responsive and comfortable. It feels fluid and flexible.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18971, 77, 99, 9.00, '2023-09-16', 'cushion', 'The bouncy cushioning is one of Nike''s best. It''s smooth and evenly distributed.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18972, 77, 10, 9.00, '2023-08-30', 'cushion', 'The cushioning feels bouncy with decent compression. Full-length Zoom Strobels are always comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18973, 77, 1, 8.00, '2023-08-12', 'cushion', 'The full-length Zoom Strobel feels comfortable and provides a lot of energy.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18974, 77, 7, 9.00, '2023-09-11', 'materials', 'The materials are thin and pliable. There''s no break-in time, which I enjoyed.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18975, 77, 111, 8.00, '2023-09-09', 'materials', 'The materials are comfortable and feel breathable. I enjoy all the materials except the toe box.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18976, 77, 2, 9.00, '2023-09-18', 'materials', 'The materials are an improvement from last year. There''s no break-in needed. The upper feels plush and comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18977, 77, 3, 8.00, '2023-09-03', 'materials', 'The upper feels better and more conforming this year. The shoe is breathable, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18978, 77, 99, 9.00, '2023-09-16', 'materials', 'I wish the heel had more padding. The tongue is padded and hugs your ankle nicely. The upper is supportive and breathable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18979, 77, 10, 9.00, '2023-08-30', 'materials', 'The materials are better quality and feel soft. The upper also feels supportive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18980, 77, 1, 8.00, '2023-08-12', 'materials', 'The shoe is more rugged and maximalist compared to the 37. I appreciate the ventilation, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18981, 77, 7, 9.50, '2023-09-11', 'support', 'The X-plate offers fantastic lateral support. The torsional rigidity is crazy, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18982, 77, 111, 9.00, '2023-09-09', 'support', 'You have to use all lace holes to avoid heel slippage. The heel lockdown and security are top-notch. Stability felt good, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18983, 77, 2, 9.00, '2023-09-18', 'support', 'The outrigger, upper materials, and stability plate keep you contained when moving from side to side.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18984, 77, 3, 8.00, '2023-09-03', 'support', 'Stability and ankle support are decent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18985, 77, 99, 8.00, '2023-09-16', 'support', 'The outrigger and X shape on the base provides stability. The torsional piece also provides rigidity.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18986, 77, 10, 8.00, '2023-08-30', 'support', 'The torsional support is impressive. The lateral containment is solid, too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18987, 77, 1, 9.00, '2023-08-12', 'support', 'I had no issues with heel slippage. The containment is excellent, and the arch support is impressive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18988, 77, 7, 9.00, '2023-09-11', 'fit', 'I enjoy the snug, 1-to-1 fit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18989, 77, 111, 8.00, '2023-09-09', 'fit', 'It feels great and conforms to your feet nicely.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18990, 77, 2, 8.00, '2023-09-18', 'fit', 'The shoe fits me well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18991, 77, 3, 8.00, '2023-09-03', 'fit', 'There''s some space in the toe box, but it doesn''t affect performance.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18992, 77, 99, 8.00, '2023-09-16', 'fit', 'The forefoot fits well, but the back half of the shoe feels snug. It pulls your foot into the shoe nicely.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18993, 77, 10, 8.00, '2023-08-30', 'fit', 'The toe box is incredibly snug. I enjoy a snug fit but had to size up for comfort.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18994, 77, 1, 8.00, '2023-08-12', 'fit', 'The fit is surprisingly pleasant.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18995, 77, 2, 0.00, '2023-09-18', 'outdoor', 'The rubber is too pliable for outdoor use.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18996, 77, 10, 50.00, '2023-08-30', 'outdoor', 'The 38s are not the best for outdoor play, but the rubber is hard.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18997, 77, 1, 0.00, '2023-08-12', 'outdoor', 'These are not good for outdoor use. The rubber wears away quickly.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18998, 77, 3, 3.00, '2023-09-03', 'width', 'The width is average.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (18999, 77, 10, 2.00, '2023-08-30', 'width', 'The width is snug.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19000, 77, 1, 3.00, '2023-08-12', 'width', '2E feet can go true to size for a performance fit or up half a size for a roomier fit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19001, 77, 2, 3.00, '2023-09-18', 'size', 'I have a regular foot and went true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19002, 77, 3, 3.00, '2023-09-03', 'size', 'My recommendation is true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19003, 77, 10, 2.00, '2023-08-30', 'size', 'I went up half a size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19004, 77, 1, 3.00, '2023-08-12', 'size', 'Narrow and medium feet can go true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19005, 78, 31, 9.50, '2023-08-16', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD is a well-balanced hoop shoe. I enjoy the comfortable cushioning, and the shoe feels like an improvement from last year.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19006, 78, 9, 8.80, '2024-03-22', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 16 is one of my favourite performers. The cushioning is catered to impact protection, and the support and materials combine to provide excellent comfort.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19007, 78, 111, 8.60, '2023-08-18', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 16 is perfect for players looking for heel impact protection and low movement latency. The traction is decent, but the cushioning is where the shoe excels.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19008, 78, 10, 8.40, '2023-08-25', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 16 feels quick. It''s a solid shoe, but there are better options on the market. The cushioning is soft, and the traction plays well on clean courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19009, 78, 7, 8.30, '2023-10-05', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 16 is a decent performer. The cushioning was a letdown compared to last year, but the support and lockdown felt fantastic.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19010, 78, 2, 8.30, '2023-09-22', 'expert_overall', 'I enjoyed playing in the Nike KD 16, even with the change in cushioning. The traction feels nice, and the shoe is supportive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19011, 78, 5, 8.20, '2023-08-18', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 16 is a well-rounded, versatile sneaker. It has traction, cushioning, and support for multiple positions and play styles.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19012, 78, 3, 8.20, '2023-09-12', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 16 doesn''t pack the same punch as previous models. It''s still a solid performer because none of the features are bad, but it''s not exceptional.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19013, 78, 6, 8.20, '2024-01-15', 'expert_overall', 'I recommend the Nike KD 16 if you''re playing on clean courts. The shoe is comfortable, and the cushioning feels incredible. Avoid playing on dusty courts, though.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19014, 78, 1, 7.80, '2023-07-24', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 16 is plush and maneuverable, but it doesn''t have the bite of the previous models.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19015, 78, 200, 8.40, '2024-02-03', 'user_overall', 'Have these in the aunt pearl colourway. Traction is insane have to wipe because of dust pick up though. Cushion is good. Bounce springy forefoot set up with zoom and the long shank plate. The air strobes and cushlon wasnt elite but was good. No large outrigger so I did roll my ankle a few times but the shoe is still fine. Chances are you wont roll your ankle unless you are in an awkward situation. Fits slightly long. Great shoe would recommend for more forwards and centers than gaurds.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19016, 78, 201, 9.20, '2024-03-01', 'user_overall', 'The KD 16 is another great performer from the KD Line. The traction is amazing on clean courts, but does pick up some dust. The cushion is the perfect cushion for a basketball shoe. A large-volume Zoom Air Unit in the fore-foot, and a Large Air unit in the heel, plus a TPU plastic shank plate give you a great mix of plush and responsive cushioning.  Support doesn''t lack anything, and keeps you locked in the shoe. The only real issue with these, is that they run narrow, so go a half size up.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19017, 78, 202, 8.90, '2024-02-18', 'user_overall', 'Great shoe overrall bud really sensitive to dust, i had to wipe every now and then when playing in dusty courts. In indoor courts and clean courts they grip like a glue on the floor! Great durability for outdoor too if you have an agile footwork type of playstyle (outer rubber is softer though than actual rubber so go xdr if playing outdoors) experience no slippage too but it''s going to be bad for wide feet as it hurts my medial side and also this shoe traps a lot of moisture!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19018, 78, 203, 8.80, '2024-04-17', 'user_overall', 'The kd 16 by no means are a bad shoe. In particular I love the colourway and performance of the shoe. However compared to previous models, like the 13s, 14s, and 15s I feel like the performance is subpar compared to the performance of the other models. But still a great shoe in the rotation.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19019, 78, 204, 8.50, '2024-01-05', 'user_overall', 'Best for players who would exchange court feel for comfort, the shoe is comfortable but as someone who wants to get the ground off quick and love court feel, this isnt the best shoe for me (court feel is not bad at all, I just like more responsiveness)');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19020, 78, 31, 9.00, '2023-08-16', 'traction', 'The traction provides solid multidirectional coverage after a break-in period, but breaking them in was rough.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (19021, 78, 9, 9.00, '2024-03-22', 'traction', 'The traction performs decently well. My translucent outsole option performed excellently on clean courts.');
