INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20336, 103, 111, 8.60, '2023-05-04', 'expert_overall', 'The Under Armour Curry 2 Low FloTro is a dope sneaker. Flow foam offers outstanding traction, but there isn''t much impact protection.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20337, 103, 3, 8.20, '2023-05-04', 'expert_overall', 'Under Armour''s FloTro line continues to deliver with the Curry 2 Low FloTro. It performs as expected, with amazing traction and court feel. The transition is smooth too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20338, 103, 266, 9.40, '2023-09-01', 'user_overall', 'This shoe is great for people with wide feet. Traction is upper "S" tier and the cushion is great if you''re a lighter individual who loves court feel and a minimalist shoe.  While The materials may be a little cheap, they''re very breathable/flexible and conform nice to the foot which help with the support aspect of the s');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20339, 103, 155, 9.00, '2024-04-13', 'user_overall', 'The shoes is nice but really slippery on dusty court. The stop on clean court is insane and sometimes I need to wear the ankle brace to not roll my ankle because of the support in this shoes kinda bad for someone have a weak ankle like me. Overall, this shoes is really nice for me and all the curry line is the best line of shoes I''ve ever hoop in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20340, 103, 272, 5.00, '2023-12-22', 'user_overall', 'Its a horrible shoe because mine broke within the first 5 minutes, it started tearing and the traction is awful on dust.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20341, 103, 273, 8.40, '2023-05-09', 'user_overall', 'Very good traction good cushioning bad outdoor playing');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20342, 103, 274, 10.00, '2023-05-15', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20343, 103, 111, 10.00, '2023-05-04', 'traction', 'The traction is beastly. Flow is the best traction compound I ever played in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20344, 103, 3, 10.00, '2023-05-04', 'traction', 'The traction performance is excellent. I never have issues with Flow model shoes.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20345, 103, 111, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'cushion', 'The Flow cushioning feels the same as the Curry 8.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20346, 103, 3, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'cushion', 'The cushioning and court feel of the shoe are identical to other Curry shoes featuring Flow. It''s soft, smooth, and comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20347, 103, 111, 9.00, '2023-05-04', 'materials', 'The shoe felt comfortable as soon as I put it on. I especially love the laces and tongue setup. The materials are lightweight and breathable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20348, 103, 3, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'materials', 'The materials are standard mesh. It''s incredibly light. You don''t feel anything on your feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20349, 103, 111, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'support', 'I had no issues with support and lockdown.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20350, 103, 3, 7.00, '2023-05-04', 'support', 'Stability and support are average, with nothing too special.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20351, 103, 111, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'fit', 'There''s a bit of give in the materials, causing the toe box to feel less snug. It didn''t affect performance much, though.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20352, 103, 3, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'fit', 'Under Armour fixed the issue with the snug toe boxes of past models. I enjoy the fit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20353, 103, 3, 3.00, '2023-05-04', 'width', 'The width is more accommodating than other Curry shoes.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20354, 103, 3, 3.00, '2023-05-04', 'size', 'The fit is true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20355, 104, 1, 8.20, '2023-05-04', 'expert_overall', 'The Adidas Trae Unlimited offers a superior ground-based game. It''s supportive and stable while feeling low to the ground. The traction caters to shifty players too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20356, 104, 10, 8.00, '2023-05-23', 'expert_overall', 'For the price, the Adidas Trae Unlimited is a comfortable shoe with no weaknesses. It doesn''t excel in any specific area, but the performance is well-rounded.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20357, 104, 115, 8.20, '2024-01-10', 'user_overall', 'Trae Unlimited is a solid ');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20358, 104, 275, 9.00, '2023-09-27', 'user_overall', 'I found it very good, and I work a lot on closed courts (wooden or cement) it is also very comfortable, I didn''t like it much outdoors and it could get damaged quickly, so only use it indoors.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20359, 104, 276, 8.70, '2024-01-14', 'user_overall', 'The tennis is really good, the anti-torsion plate is quite efficient, the tennis rubber is softer on the forefoot, while the heel is quite resistant, the support is quite noticeable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20360, 104, 277, 7.50, '2024-02-07', 'user_overall', 'Traction pretty mid.U gotta wipe on every single play');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20361, 104, 50, 7.80, '2024-09-04', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20362, 104, 1, 9.00, '2023-05-04', 'traction', 'I like the design of the outsole tread. The grip and cornering are fantastic, but it could be better with straight-line traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20363, 104, 10, 8.00, '2023-05-23', 'traction', 'The traction is damn sticky on clean courts, but dust negatively affects the performance.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20364, 104, 1, 7.00, '2023-05-04', 'cushion', 'The cushioning uses Bounce foam. It isn''t the bounciest, but it feels low to the ground.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20365, 104, 10, 8.00, '2023-05-23', 'cushion', 'The Bounce foam feels soft, and the impact protection is there. There''s a bit of bounciness too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20366, 104, 1, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'materials', 'The upper is thick and padded. It needs a bit of breaking in and isn''t the most breathable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20367, 104, 10, 8.00, '2023-05-23', 'materials', 'The materials are middle of the pack. The quality isn''t the best, but the performance is solid.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20368, 104, 1, 9.00, '2023-05-04', 'support', 'The built-in runner''s knot eyelet helps keep your ankle and foot locked in. The stability is also solid.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20369, 104, 10, 8.00, '2023-05-23', 'support', 'I felt contained laterally. The torsional support is solid too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20370, 104, 1, 8.00, '2023-05-04', 'fit', 'The fit is accommodating for most foot shapes.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20371, 104, 10, 8.00, '2023-05-23', 'fit', 'The fit feels normal.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20372, 104, 1, 0.00, '2023-05-04', 'outdoor', 'The shoe is better for indoor surfaces.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20373, 104, 10, 50.00, '2023-05-23', 'outdoor', 'The rubber feels hard enough for outdoor use.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20374, 104, 10, 3.00, '2023-05-23', 'width', 'The width feels normal too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20375, 104, 10, 3.00, '2023-05-23', 'size', 'I went true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20376, 105, 7, 9.40, '2023-03-21', 'expert_overall', 'You can''t go wrong with the Nike LeBron NXXT Gen at this price point. The traction is top-tier, the Zoom units feel fantastic, and the support is outstanding.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20377, 105, 103, 9.00, '2023-04-16', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike LeBron NXXT Gen is an awesome basketball shoe. It''s quick, responsive, and stable, and the fit is dead on.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20378, 105, 10, 8.80, '2023-04-13', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike LeBron NXXT Gen feels light, responsive, and quick. The traction performance is fantastic, and the cushioning does everything well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20379, 105, 111, 8.40, '2023-03-12', 'expert_overall', 'I like the Nike LeBron NXXT Gen better than the LeBron 20. I recommend the shoe for all players. It performed better than expected because of the comfortable materials and tacky traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20380, 105, 3, 8.40, '2023-04-13', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike LeBron NXXT Gen is an A-tier shoe. The cushioning isn''t as bouncy but stable, and the traction provides good stopping power.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20381, 105, 1, 8.20, '2023-02-08', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike LeBron NXXT Gen is a solid option for forwards who don''t need maximalist cushioning setups. The cushioning is comfortable, and the materials play well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20382, 105, 278, 8.50, '2024-02-17', 'user_overall', 'The Lebron nxxt gen is a sturdy performer but doesnt fit my playstyle all that well. I wouldve liked more responsive and low to the ground cushioning and wouldve avoided all that forefoot cushion because for me its a bit much. On extremely dusty courts the traction is not good but on clean courts its incredible. Me personally Im a bit disappointed with the Lebron nxxt gen as it just didnt fit my personal playstyle as a point guard but I would definitely recommend it for heavier players');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20383, 105, 214, 8.60, '2023-05-25', 'user_overall', 'Even without the $40 price decrease, I thought the NXXT Gen outperformed the XX on court. They kept the great combo zoom setup, but made a few changes around it. The thick, soft cushlon was swapped out for a firmer phylon, greatly increasing courtfeel while still providing good impact protection. The bottom loaded CF shank was swapped out for a top loaded TPE shank, but still gives plenty of return and support. Traction is still great. They are lighter than the XX, and feel much quicker on foot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20384, 105, 279, 9.60, '2024-04-15', 'user_overall', 'The Lebron NXXT gen was easily one of the best basketball shoes in the many I''ve worn as a basketball player. I''m a shifty guard, who stops on a dime often and these shoes provided excellent traction to help out with that. The materials and cushioning were extremely durable. However, I did notice the front of the shoe started to peel off a little due to some rigorous use and a little slippage at the start. Other than that, the shoe was excellent and easily one of the best I''ve used.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20385, 105, 280, 8.30, '2024-03-22', 'user_overall', 'When I first got this shoe I thought it was pretty good and just a solid basketball shoe that I can use to play. I play mainly outdoor cause there aren''t many indoor places to hoop near me. I have flat feet so every time I play with them they always hurt my feet and I get a lot of pain. Im no expert on rating basketball shoes but i feel like the traction on these aren''t the best, neither is the comfort. The only thing that I truly like about them specifically is the support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20386, 105, 281, 8.60, '2023-04-18', 'user_overall', 'great shoe overall but its slightly narrow and the translucent outsole picks up a lot of dust. id also recommend going half a size up cause the shoe runs small. other than that the shoe does not really have any flaws. the materials are not as good as the lebron 20s but they get the job done. the traction is amazing and the zoom turbo units provide alot of bounce. id say this is definitely a better option than the lebron 20s because of the 40$ price difference.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20387, 105, 7, 9.00, '2023-03-21', 'traction', 'The traction performed amazingly well on clean and dirty courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20388, 105, 103, 9.00, '2023-04-16', 'traction', 'The traction performance feels the same as the LeBron 20. It''s just below the top tier, which is impressive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20389, 105, 10, 10.00, '2023-04-13', 'traction', 'You don''t have to worry about the traction on clean courts. The performance is top-tier. It''s an easy wipe on dusty courts too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20390, 105, 111, 9.00, '2023-03-12', 'traction', 'The traction was beastly, even on dirty floors. These are just below elite but still top-tier.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20391, 105, 3, 9.00, '2023-04-13', 'traction', 'The traction is grippy and isn''t affected by dust as long as you wipe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20392, 105, 1, 8.00, '2023-02-08', 'traction', 'The traction is fluid and easy to get from one spot to the next. The downside is that it doesn''t stop like the LeBron 20.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20393, 105, 7, 9.50, '2023-03-21', 'cushion', 'The cushioning feels similar to the LeBron 20. The foam feels firmer, but the Zoom units provide impact protection and responsiveness.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20394, 105, 103, 8.00, '2023-04-16', 'cushion', 'The cushioning is stable and responsive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20395, 105, 10, 9.00, '2023-04-13', 'cushion', 'The cushioning offers a decent court feel without sacrificing impact protection. It does this while still being bouncy.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20396, 105, 111, 8.00, '2023-03-12', 'cushion', 'The foam feels stiff to the touch, but underfoot the cushioning feels great. I prefer to feel bouncier, but it''s still a solid performer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20397, 105, 3, 8.00, '2023-04-13', 'cushion', 'The heel impact protection is less plush but more stable. The shoe loses some bounciness to the LeBron 20 too. It''s responsive, though.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20398, 105, 1, 9.00, '2023-02-08', 'cushion', 'The foam feels like the Cushlon used in the LeBron 20s. The Zoom units are also the same, but the shank plate is plastic instead of carbon fibre. It''s slightly less bouncy but just as comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20399, 105, 7, 8.50, '2023-03-21', 'materials', 'The upper is screen mesh, and it feels like a downgrade. It''s still durable, though.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20400, 105, 103, 9.00, '2023-04-16', 'materials', 'The materials feel soft and comfortable. Despite the tight fit, I didn''t experience any pain.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20401, 105, 10, 8.00, '2023-04-13', 'materials', 'The materials are thin, soft, and supportive. I like how it feels around my foot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20402, 105, 111, 9.00, '2023-03-12', 'materials', 'The materials around the heel feel comfortable. The sneaker is breathable and feels great around the foot too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20403, 105, 3, 8.00, '2023-04-13', 'materials', 'The materials feel plasticky but are thin and soft.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20404, 105, 1, 8.00, '2023-02-08', 'materials', 'The materials are engineered mesh. It''s a combination of textile and TPU threads. It feels contained and is surprisingly strong. The tongue isn''t as padded, though.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20405, 105, 7, 10.00, '2023-03-21', 'support', 'The support feels absolutely amazing. The materials contain you laterally. It feels like a straitjacket on feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20406, 105, 103, 9.00, '2023-04-16', 'support', 'Lockdown in the shoe feels perfect. The lateral stability is solid too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20407, 105, 10, 8.00, '2023-04-13', 'support', 'Torsional support isn''t the best, but it didn''t bother me. The lateral containment felt supportive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20408, 105, 111, 8.00, '2023-03-12', 'support', 'There is no heel slippage in this shoe. I felt locked down, and I had no slippage or side-to-side movement.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20409, 105, 3, 9.00, '2023-04-13', 'support', 'The stability is improved in the NXXT Gen compared to the LeBron 20. The lockdown is secure too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20410, 105, 1, 8.00, '2023-02-08', 'support', 'The containment of the shoe is impressive because of the materials.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20411, 105, 7, 10.00, '2023-03-21', 'fit', 'With the right size, there is no dead space. It''s a 1-to-1 fit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20412, 105, 103, 10.00, '2023-04-16', 'fit', 'My favourite attribute of the shoe is the fit. It feels tight and snug.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20413, 105, 10, 9.00, '2023-04-13', 'fit', 'The upper conforms well to your foot after breaking in the shoe. It feels perfect after playing for a while.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (20414, 105, 111, 8.00, '2023-03-12', 'fit', 'The tongue conforms to your feet well. I have no bad things to say about the fit.');
