INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27830, 303, 176, 9.50, '2018-04-17', 'expert_overall', 'It may be an opinion clouded in sentiment, but there is no denying it: the Protro is a great, great, great performer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27831, 303, 32, 9.40, '2018-04-26', 'expert_overall', 'I miss shoes that are built like this. Nike reduced a bit of bulk from the original and created a shoe that I didn''t want to take off again.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27832, 303, 6, 9.00, '2018-10-01', 'expert_overall', 'At $175, I wouldn''t really recommend the Kobe Protro for on-court use. This is a great performer, but there are cheaper shoes that perform just as well. If you are a big Kobe fan or you like the old school materials, then go ahead and buy these!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27833, 303, 522, 8.80, '2018-08-08', 'expert_overall', 'The Kobe 1 Protro feels and plays like the OG which is a good thing! From traction to containment and balanced cushioning - it does everything right and gets a first-team rating from me!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27834, 303, 221, 8.50, '2018-04-30', 'expert_overall', 'At the end of the day, the Kobe 1 Protro still feels like a throwback sneaker. The materials feel heavy and restrictive compared to current basketball shoe models.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27835, 303, 293, 8.40, '2018-04-30', 'expert_overall', 'The Kobe 1 Protro is a decent big-man shoe. But for me, it was way too clunky and heavy. I feel like this is more of a lifestyle sneaker.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27836, 303, 729, 8.90, '2023-04-28', 'user_overall', 'Leather upper very supportive but unbreathable. Too heavy and bulky shoe for shifty guards. But traction, air zoom cushioning, materials quality, support patterns is AMAZING. Slightly long shoe btw.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27837, 303, 222, 8.20, '2023-05-26', 'user_overall', 'Its pretty bulky, the cushion is stiff and the traction is nice but not top notch. Is really a beautiful shoe, but i wouldnt consider it a great performer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27838, 303, 552, 10.00, '2021-11-06', 'user_overall', 'Just my kinda shoes, but it''s heavy and not very breathable due to the material use, but loves it in terms of traction, cushion and kobe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27839, 303, 651, 7.80, '2022-03-30', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27840, 303, 176, 10.00, '2018-04-17', 'traction', 'The Kobe 1 Protro sticks like glue to any floor.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27841, 303, 32, 9.50, '2018-04-26', 'traction', 'Its the tackiest of tractions it grips the court  any court  like nobodys business.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27842, 303, 6, 9.00, '2018-10-01', 'traction', 'Herringbone traction pattern always works. Whether I played on clean or dusty courts, I had no problems after a short break-in period.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27843, 303, 522, 9.00, '2018-08-08', 'traction', 'The traction takes a little to break in but Nike did an awesome job with this multi-directional herringbone pattern.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27844, 303, 221, 8.00, '2018-04-30', 'traction', 'The outsole isn''t as tacky as I would have liked it to be.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27845, 303, 293, 8.00, '2018-04-30', 'traction', 'The traction wasn''t as good as I hoped it would be.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27846, 303, 176, 9.50, '2018-04-17', 'cushion', 'Nike Zoom Ari cushioning like it was originally designed to be: low, fast, speedy and responsive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27847, 303, 32, 9.50, '2018-04-26', 'cushion', 'The full-length Zoom Air here is low-to-the-ground, ultra responsive and has some nice feedback.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27848, 303, 6, 9.50, '2018-10-01', 'cushion', 'Full-length Zoom is my favorite cushioning setup and it feels amazing in the Kobe Protro.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27849, 303, 522, 9.00, '2018-08-08', 'cushion', 'I thoroughly enjoyed the full-length Zoom cushioning which provides a great blend of fun, impact protection, and court feel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27850, 303, 221, 9.00, '2018-04-30', 'cushion', 'This is a very versatile cushioning setup which is very responsive, fast, with decent impact protection. Perfect for explosive wing players.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27851, 303, 293, 9.00, '2018-04-30', 'cushion', 'The cushioning feels very responsive and fast.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27852, 303, 176, 9.50, '2018-04-17', 'materials', 'This is it: leather, suede, and leather, and more suede. Takes a while to break-in but then it feels great.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27853, 303, 32, 10.00, '2018-04-26', 'materials', 'I had forgotten just how nice leather is to play in!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27854, 303, 6, 9.00, '2018-10-01', 'materials', 'Super-nice, old-school, real leather.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27855, 303, 522, 8.00, '2018-08-08', 'materials', 'The leather and suede are a little stiffer than the original and need some time to break in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27856, 303, 293, 9.00, '2018-04-30', 'materials', 'The leather is very soft and feels great on foot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27857, 303, 176, 9.50, '2018-04-17', 'support', 'Wide base, large outrigger, lateral support from foam teeth on the lateral side of the midsole and the sturdy leather provide all the support you need.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27858, 303, 32, 9.00, '2018-04-26', 'support', 'Tthe forefoot stability is some of the best around  maybe even of all-time.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27859, 303, 6, 8.50, '2018-10-01', 'support', 'I experienced slight heel slippage even when cranking down the laces. No side-to-side movement on the footbed, great torsional stability, and the lateral outriggers protect your ankles from rolling.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27860, 303, 522, 9.00, '2018-08-08', 'support', 'The ankle is very flexible and provides you with a wide range of motion but not a ton of support. The outsole is very wide and flat which helps to prevent ankle sprains.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27861, 303, 221, 10.00, '2018-04-30', 'support', 'If you feel like basketball shoes are too flimsy these days, then you will enjoy the Kobe 1 Protro because the materials are tough enough for even the most explosive players.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27862, 303, 293, 9.00, '2018-04-30', 'support', 'Your feet are going nowhere in these shoes!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27863, 303, 176, 9.00, '2018-04-17', 'fit', 'In the beginning, the shoe will feel bulky and disconnected because the leather takes a while to conform to your feet. Fit becomes much better after playing in the Kobe 1 Protro for a few days.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27864, 303, 32, 9.00, '2018-04-26', 'fit', 'Once the leather is broken-in the fit was great and almost provided the mobility of a low-cut.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27865, 303, 6, 9.00, '2018-10-01', 'fit', 'Hugs my feet nicely and the leather feels comfortable after breaking it in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27866, 303, 522, 9.00, '2018-08-08', 'fit', 'No heel slip. No movement side to side. Well done Nike!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27867, 303, 221, 7.00, '2018-04-30', 'fit', 'Even though I spent a ton of time trying to lace the Kobe 1 Proto as tight as possible, I didn''t feel locked-in because the leather didn''t conform to my feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27868, 303, 293, 7.00, '2018-04-30', 'fit', 'I felt the fit was bulky and cumbersome.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27869, 303, 293, 100.00, '2018-04-30', 'outdoor', 'Outdoor use should be good because of the hard and thick rubber.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27870, 303, 6, 2.00, '2018-10-01', 'width', 'Slightly narrow in the forefoot but loosens up over time.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27871, 303, 293, 4.00, '2018-04-30', 'width', 'The Kobe 1 Proto runs wide.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27872, 303, 6, 3.00, '2018-10-01', 'size', 'Runs true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27873, 303, 522, 4.00, '2018-08-08', 'size', 'I went down half a size and they fit me just fine.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27874, 303, 293, 3.00, '2018-04-30', 'size', 'Runs true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27875, 304, 615, 9.50, '2018-04-30', 'expert_overall', 'Overall, the Kobe NXT 360 is the best Kobe shoe since the Kobe 9, in my opinion.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27876, 304, 293, 9.40, '2018-04-25', 'expert_overall', 'There is no other shoe I want to play in as much as these. Even though the traction of the translucent rubber is not the best this still might be the best basketball shoe we ever played in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27877, 304, 6, 9.20, '2018-07-16', 'expert_overall', 'The Kobe AD NXT 360 is a great performer and looks amazing!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27878, 304, 44, 8.80, '2018-09-26', 'expert_overall', 'This is officially PureKicks best-rated shoe so far!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27879, 304, 32, 8.60, '2018-06-16', 'expert_overall', 'The Kobe NXT 360 is a true next-generation shoe and incredibly fun to play in!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27880, 304, 31, 8.50, '2018-04-24', 'expert_overall', 'The traction is subpar, the 360 Flyknit concept is cool but nothing spectacular and the price is too expensive for what you get.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27881, 304, 221, 8.40, '2018-06-12', 'expert_overall', 'I absolutely loved playing in these shoes! The Kobe AD NXT 360 truly feels like a high-performance shoe with cutting-edge technology and will be in my rotation for a long time.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27882, 304, 522, 8.40, '2018-07-16', 'expert_overall', 'So is the NXT 360 worth the price of admission? In a nutshell, no. The Mamba Instinct delivers similar performance, at a fraction of the price!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27883, 304, 458, 10.00, '2023-04-20', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27884, 304, 730, 9.20, '2023-05-17', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27885, 304, 731, 9.00, '2022-02-06', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27886, 304, 324, 8.20, '2022-02-19', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27887, 304, 651, 9.20, '2022-03-30', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27888, 304, 615, 9.00, '2018-04-30', 'traction', 'The traction wasnt bad, but it wasnt the best either. Works well on clean courts but dusty courts are problematic.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27889, 304, 293, 7.00, '2018-04-25', 'traction', 'The translucent traction pattern attracted a lot of dust and required tough wiping. On clean courts the traction was good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27890, 304, 6, 9.50, '2018-07-16', 'traction', 'The traction is phenomenal even on dustier courts!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27891, 304, 44, 9.00, '2018-09-26', 'traction', 'You don''t have to worry about slipping or sliding at all.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27892, 304, 32, 9.00, '2018-06-16', 'traction', 'Traction on the Kobe NXT 360 started out phenomenally but has already lost some of its grip after 4 weeks of use.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27893, 304, 31, 7.00, '2018-04-24', 'traction', 'The traction doesn''t grip the floor very well even after breaking them in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27894, 304, 221, 7.00, '2018-06-12', 'traction', 'The rubber compound isn''t very sticky but did a decent job. On a dusty court you will need to wipe, but then you''re good to go.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27895, 304, 522, 8.00, '2018-07-16', 'traction', 'Traction was a bit disappointing as It didnt have the bite I was expecting on clean floors and picked up a decent amount of dust.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27896, 304, 615, 10.00, '2018-04-30', 'cushion', 'The comfort is there, the impact protection is there, the court feel is there  the stuff is just amazing.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27897, 304, 293, 10.00, '2018-04-25', 'cushion', 'The best cushioning setup we have ever experienced. Nike just nailed it!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27898, 304, 6, 9.00, '2018-07-16', 'cushion', 'This is one of my favorite cushioning setups and comes really close to full-length Zoom.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27899, 304, 44, 10.00, '2018-09-26', 'cushion', 'The mixture of Nike React and Lunarlon feels absolutely incredible.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27900, 304, 32, 9.00, '2018-06-16', 'cushion', 'The mixed React and Lunarlon drop-in midsole provides a fluid ride with a lot of court-feel in the front and impact protection in the rear.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27901, 304, 31, 8.00, '2018-04-24', 'cushion', 'Nike Lunarlon combined with React cushioning is solid but I like more responsive cushioning like Nike Zoom Air.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27902, 304, 221, 8.00, '2018-06-12', 'cushion', 'Very low to the ground, responsive and a ton of court feel. If you need a lot of impact protection - this is not for you.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27903, 304, 522, 9.00, '2018-07-16', 'cushion', 'If you want low to the ground yet comfortable and balanced cushioning, then this is your set up.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27904, 304, 615, 9.50, '2018-04-30', 'materials', 'I''m almost speechless because the materials are so nice!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27905, 304, 293, 10.00, '2018-04-25', 'materials', 'The upper is incredibly minimal, doesn''t stretch and provides very good ventilation.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27906, 304, 6, 9.50, '2018-07-16', 'materials', 'The pure 360 Flyknit in the rear feels amazing, the front is TPU reinforced to provide more lockdown and durability.  Being able to see through the upper is really cool and unique.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27907, 304, 44, 9.00, '2018-09-26', 'materials', 'The materials are probably the most comfortable I ever experienced in a basketball shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27908, 304, 32, 7.00, '2018-06-16', 'materials', '360-degrees of Flyknit was hyped up quite a bit. It performs well, but it wasnt anything spectacular.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27909, 304, 221, 10.00, '2018-06-12', 'materials', 'The extremely lightweight and flexible 360 Flyknit material is truly cutting edge and feels like an extension of your feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27910, 304, 522, 8.00, '2018-07-16', 'materials', 'TPU reinforced Flyknit is very breathable and comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27911, 304, 615, 9.50, '2018-04-30', 'support', 'The support comes mainly drom the drop-in midsole and is fantastic.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27912, 304, 293, 10.00, '2018-04-25', 'support', 'No heel slippage, great containment, and lateral support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27913, 304, 6, 9.00, '2018-07-16', 'support', 'Zero heel slippage, no side-to-side movement. I just would have wished to get a lateral outrigger.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27914, 304, 44, 8.00, '2018-09-26', 'support', 'The support is very, very good considering the minimal build of the upper.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27915, 304, 32, 9.00, '2018-06-16', 'support', 'For  $200 I would have liked a few more support features like an external outrigger or a mid-foot carbon fiber plate.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27916, 304, 31, 8.00, '2018-04-24', 'support', 'The support was surprisingly good considering the type of construction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27917, 304, 221, 8.00, '2018-06-12', 'support', 'Stability is not an issue with the Kobe AD NXT 360!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27918, 304, 522, 7.00, '2018-07-16', 'support', 'Support is fine for a low top with excellent heel fit and a decent heel counter. However, the rounded outsole with no outrigger is just asking me for an ankle sprain.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27919, 304, 615, 9.50, '2018-04-30', 'fit', 'Great lockdown and very good ventilation.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27920, 304, 293, 10.00, '2018-04-25', 'fit', 'This is the best fitting shoe I have ever worn!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27921, 304, 6, 9.00, '2018-07-16', 'fit', 'Nice 1:1 fit, no complaints at all!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27922, 304, 44, 8.00, '2018-09-26', 'fit', 'The fit of this shoe is very good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27923, 304, 32, 9.00, '2018-06-16', 'fit', 'Lockdown was surprisingly good, and if you get the right size, then this shoe feels like an extension of your foot!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27924, 304, 221, 9.00, '2018-06-12', 'fit', 'The fit is awesome - I had a second skin experience!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27925, 304, 522, 10.00, '2018-07-16', 'fit', 'Great heel lockdown, no dead space in the toe box, no side-to-side movement and the thin upper feels like a second skin. The fit is the highlight of the 360 -  no doubt!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27926, 304, 293, 0.00, '2018-04-25', 'outdoor', 'Outdoor use is not recommended.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27927, 304, 6, 0.00, '2018-07-16', 'outdoor', 'The rubber is pretty soft and the pattern is too narrow for outdoor use.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27928, 304, 44, 0.00, '2018-09-26', 'outdoor', 'I would definitely not take these outdoors.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27929, 304, 293, 2.00, '2018-04-25', 'width', 'The width is pretty narrow.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27930, 304, 6, 3.00, '2018-07-16', 'width', 'I have slightly wide feet but the Kobe AD NXT 360 didn''t bother me in my true size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27931, 304, 44, 3.00, '2018-09-26', 'width', 'The shoe will conform to the shape of your feet and worked perfectly fine for my wide feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27932, 304, 293, 4.00, '2018-04-25', 'size', 'They run long, go down half a size!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27933, 304, 6, 3.00, '2018-07-16', 'size', 'Go true to size, even if you have slightly wide feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27934, 304, 44, 3.00, '2018-09-26', 'size', 'True-to-size fit me perfectly well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27935, 304, 522, 4.00, '2018-07-16', 'size', 'I went true to size with the 360 and it has a tiny bit of extra length in the toe but not enough to size down half a size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27936, 305, 293, 9.00, '2018-06-12', 'expert_overall', 'The Lebron Soldier 12 is 100% worth its price! It''s just nice to play in a shoe with gnarly traction like this!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27937, 305, 522, 8.60, '2018-09-26', 'expert_overall', 'If you want a shoe that does everything very well, this is your shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27938, 305, 44, 7.40, '2018-06-12', 'expert_overall', 'The traction was surprisingly fantastic! The fit was brillitant, the support was good, if only the materials would have been better!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27939, 305, 504, 7.60, '2022-01-05', 'user_overall', 'The shoe was good indoors, for more of a big man in the paint than a PG or SG. However durability is terrible. After 2 months of playing indoors/outdoors the bubble in the midsole came out of the bottoms that''s how much rubber came off...');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27940, 305, 458, 6.80, '2023-04-07', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27941, 305, 732, 8.40, '2023-12-30', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27942, 305, 293, 10.00, '2018-06-12', 'traction', 'The traction is absolutely amazing, even on dusty courts!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27943, 305, 522, 9.00, '2018-09-26', 'traction', 'The pliable rubber with a simple blade pattern just works on every surface with minimal wiping.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27944, 305, 44, 9.00, '2018-06-12', 'traction', 'The traction really bit the floor even on dusty courts!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27945, 305, 293, 7.00, '2018-06-12', 'cushion', 'Bottom-loaded heel and forefoot Zoom in a firm Phylon midsole. Impact protection is decent, courtfeel is not great as you feel pretty high up.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27946, 305, 522, 8.00, '2018-09-26', 'cushion', 'Overall, Im happy with how the Soldier XII feels underfoot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27947, 305, 44, 8.00, '2018-06-12', 'cushion', 'With forefoot Zoom and heel Zoom you are taken care off!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27948, 305, 293, 9.00, '2018-06-12', 'materials', 'Neoprene-like material around the midfoot and canvas / leather depending on the colorway on the forefoot. It''s not as premium as the Battleknit on the Lebron 15, but still really nice!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27949, 305, 522, 9.00, '2018-09-26', 'materials', 'The synthetic leather feels very premium and the knit looks very similar to Battleknit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27950, 305, 44, 5.00, '2018-06-12', 'materials', 'The straps weren''t holding up - we had to restrap all the time which was pretty annoying. Also the ventilation was pretty bad.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27951, 305, 293, 10.00, '2018-06-12', 'support', 'The straps of the Lebron 12 give you a very nice lockdown, no heel slippage or lateral movement.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27952, 305, 522, 8.00, '2018-09-26', 'support', 'Support is average with a pretty flexible sock like upper.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27953, 305, 44, 7.00, '2018-06-12', 'support', 'Heel counter, outrigger, and nice lockdown are there. Feels like a low top, but the support is good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27954, 305, 522, 9.00, '2018-09-26', 'fit', 'The fit is very good overall with the Soldier XII without any heel slip or wide to side movement and no dead space in the forefoot at all.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27955, 305, 44, 8.00, '2018-06-12', 'fit', 'Fits like an glove and requires minimal break-in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27956, 305, 293, 50.00, '2018-06-12', 'outdoor', 'You could get away with it, if you really want to.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27957, 305, 44, 100.00, '2018-06-12', 'outdoor', 'Hard rubber, deep grooves - what more do you want?');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27958, 305, 522, 3.00, '2018-09-26', 'size', 'True to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27959, 305, 44, 3.00, '2018-06-12', 'size', 'Go true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27960, 306, 293, 8.20, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'This is by far the cheapest signature model on the market but it''s still a very good performer. We enjoyed it a lot!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27961, 306, 31, 7.50, '2018-04-24', 'expert_overall', 'Considering that the Kyrie Flytrap is a budget model it gets the job done, but it''s nothing spectacular. Save some extra money and get the Kyrie 4.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27962, 306, 32, 7.40, '2018-04-17', 'expert_overall', 'Not a bad shoe for $80, but I would opt for discounted Kyrie 4s  unless you happen to have a wide foot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27963, 306, 649, 6.80, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'I can''t recommend the Kyrie Flytrap from a performance standpoint. The Flytrap feels so cheap that it doesnt even feel like it was made by Nike.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27964, 306, 615, 6.70, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'Is it worth your $80 bucks? I dont think so.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27965, 306, 729, 7.20, '2023-04-28', 'user_overall', 'If you are a looking cheap outdoor shoe, flytrap series good option for you. Good for shifty guards who dont need cushion. But materials and fit line is so bad.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27966, 306, 733, 8.00, '2022-12-29', 'user_overall', 'Good shoe to play in especially outdoors. It''s mainly for guards, it focuses on response than impact protection');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27967, 306, 686, 7.80, '2022-02-22', 'user_overall', 'Great for wide footers and this is the only shoe that the traction got worse each time i played in it.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27968, 306, 233, 7.40, '2023-12-28', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (27969, 306, 651, 7.80, '2021-11-29', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28017, 308, 31, 9.00, '2018-03-04', 'expert_overall', 'The PG2 has slightly improved in every aspect: better cushioning, nicer materials, more comfortable fit and slightly improved traction make them a contender for best shoe of 2018.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28018, 308, 615, 9.00, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike PG 2 is a well-rounded shoe and great for people all shapes and sizes. Id say its definitely an upgrade from the PG 1.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28019, 308, 176, 9.00, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'The PG2 is honestly the best all-around shoe that Nike has on the market right now (especially at $110).');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28020, 308, 6, 8.60, '2018-02-26', 'expert_overall', 'The PG2 performs well across all aspects and comes at an extremely fair price.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28021, 308, 221, 8.60, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike PG2 is a slight improvement over the PG1 and in the competition for the best bang-for-the-buck basketball shoe on the market.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28022, 308, 522, 8.40, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike PG2 is all any player would need, everything about it is solid.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28023, 308, 649, 8.30, '2018-08-08', 'expert_overall', 'Lockdown and fit have been greatly improved, the cushioning offers exceptional response after a break-in period and $110 remains a great deal! Unfortunately, the shoe still isn''t the most comfortable and traction has taken a small step backward.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28024, 308, 293, 8.20, '2018-03-04', 'expert_overall', 'At this price point, you will have a hard time finding another shoe of this quality.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28025, 308, 44, 8.00, '2018-03-25', 'expert_overall', 'This shoe is an absolute steal! I especially loved the incredible fit and traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28026, 308, 735, 9.60, '2022-11-16', 'user_overall', 'Overall fit is great which really gave ton of support for my foot. Cushion is stiff and lacking on heel comfort but super responsive and amazing court feel. Durability is pretty excellect due to foam type and suede materials which gave premium and old school aesthetics. Traction does have a good bite although durability of the outsole is my major concern. It really burns quickly the traction pattern of the shoe.   I think the shoe is perfect for players with smooth style of play like PG himself.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28027, 308, 14, 8.40, '2022-11-17', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28028, 308, 472, 8.00, '2023-12-28', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (28029, 308, 736, 8.50, '2022-01-09', 'user_overall', NULL);
