INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29060, 329, 615, 9.30, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Overall, the Nike Lebron Soldier 11 is the bomb, I love it! I have no complaints about it whatsoever. This shoe jumped up to #2 on my rotation, that''s how much I liked it.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29061, 329, 32, 8.60, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'While traction could still use a little bit of work, the cushion is immensely better than the last go-around. Suitable for every position on the floor and a great option for players than want a little bit of everything with their on-court shoes.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29062, 329, 293, 8.60, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'A well-rounded shoe that provides a ton of support and lockdown. Traction is decent. Not recommended for shifty guards because it feels a little bulky, but a very good shoe for bigger players who value impact protection, lockdown and support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29063, 329, 522, 8.60, '2017-12-27', 'expert_overall', 'Although the Soldier XI doesnt do anything extremely well, its a very solid shoe all the way around.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29064, 329, 649, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The LeBron Soldier 11 in many ways is just the LeBron Soldier 10.1. Thats really not a bad thing though, as the Soldier 10 was a great shoe, and the 11 improves on almost every aspect of its design with very minimal compromise.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29065, 329, 486, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Good for what it does, doesn''t quite get the Kick Genius stamp of approval but definitely gets the job done. The best Lebron Soldier I ever played in for sure.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29066, 329, 755, 8.20, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike LeBron Soldier 11 is a very versatile sneaker. Any guard or slashing forward will find something that they like. It is a solid option both indoors and on the black top, yet it isnt quite elite. Had Nike went all out on the cushioning and made it a little more stable, it would have easily been a top-tier performer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29067, 329, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'It''s a really, really solid shoe. I loved the cushioning and responsiveness, the support and lockdown were really solid, but traction was very inconsistent. Not my go-to shoes but definitely in the rotation.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29068, 329, 201, 8.00, '2023-09-23', 'user_overall', 'this shoe has the best support I''ve probably ever played in. The cushion is there but felt very little. the traction in one word is well, inconsistent. On a dusty court you''re slipping and sliding, and on a clean court you either have amazing grip or you''re still slipping. This shoe is a bit bulky and I recommend for larger forwards or wing players.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29069, 329, 758, 9.60, '2023-07-06', 'user_overall', 'Great for a bouncy wing. Have had 3 pair of these for 5+ years and they are all in great shape with no issues, except velcro failing.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29070, 329, 576, 9.40, '2022-02-07', 'user_overall', 'Amazing shoes have beautiful strap confortable..');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29071, 329, 403, 9.00, '2022-11-06', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29072, 329, 759, 8.60, '2022-12-22', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29073, 329, 615, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'After the shoes broke in the traction was really awesome.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29074, 329, 32, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'While the traction on the Nike LeBron Soldier 11 isnt bad, it isnt as good as it should be.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29075, 329, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Traction is very nice on clean courts, but picks up a fair amount of dust.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29076, 329, 522, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'traction', 'It has a surprising bite and held up even on dusty floors without much wiping at all.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29077, 329, 649, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction of the Soldier 11, on the other had, is actually good. Youll have to swipe occasionally, like almost every shoe, but after a very brief break-in period, the grip was squeaky and secure.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29078, 329, 486, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'If you are in dustier setting your are going to slide all over the place. On clean courts traction is really good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29079, 329, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction on the LeBron Soldier 11 is surprisingly solid but not very consistent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29080, 329, 31, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction was pretty inconsistent. Good on clean courts, but horrible on really dusty courts. Even Lebron slipped in these during the finals.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29081, 329, 615, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Protruding Nike Zoom Units in the forefoot and heel felt amazing.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29082, 329, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The Zoom Air units are pretty damn big which means impact protection is solid overall.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29083, 329, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'You get a ton of response because the cushion is pretty firm.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29084, 329, 522, 8.00, '2017-12-27', 'cushion', 'There is a decent amount of bounce to the Zoom but still not as lively as my standard, the Soldier VI.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29085, 329, 649, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The dual-Zoom bag setup is better implemented than in the Soldier 10 and provides a noticeable improvement.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29086, 329, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Zoom Air in both the heel and forefoot performs admirably - it just would have been so much better with full-length Zoom.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29087, 329, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The cushion is pretty standard but responsiveness is great.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29088, 329, 615, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Materials look so nice, I don''t even want to hoop in these. But breathability is not existent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29089, 329, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Materials offer the feeling of wearing a knit/woven upper but with a bit more strength.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29090, 329, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Materials feel better than in the Soldier 10 but are still relatively cheap.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29091, 329, 522, 8.00, '2017-12-27', 'materials', 'Nothing fancy, just plain old mesh.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29092, 329, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The  suede overlay of the "premium version of the LeBron Soldier 11 is too nice to pass up.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29093, 329, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The materials are nothing special. The upper is soft and comfortable but breathability is a problem');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29094, 329, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Is the shoes fit supportive enough without laces being involved? Yes, at least for me.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29095, 329, 293, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'The upper is very supportive and doesn''t stretch, lateral support is great and ankle support is decent too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29096, 329, 522, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'support', 'Thanks to a low-to-the-ground ride, flat outsole and double outrigger the Lebron Soldier is very stable and supportive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29097, 329, 649, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Sculpted collar padding, along with the external heel counter and forefoot outriggers, combine to create confidence in the shoes stability.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29098, 329, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'The four straps gave me extra confidence while recovering from an ankle sprain.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29099, 329, 755, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'This is the first time that Ive ever felt like a LeBron sneaker needed more support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29100, 329, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Lockdown is great. At times I felt a little wobbly because of the narrow base, but overall I didn''t have any problems with support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29101, 329, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The shoes are a little hard to get on, lockdown on the shoe was good and once the materials are broke in a bit things started to feel secure.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29102, 329, 293, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Once you get your feet in, the straps lock down you feet really right, I love it!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29103, 329, 522, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'fit', 'I had no movement side to side or front to back, no heel slip, well done Nike!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29104, 329, 649, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The Soldier 11 is essentially a sock with some straps. But similar to the Soldier 10, it actually fits well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29105, 329, 755, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Out of the box these shoes have an extremely snug but comfortable fit. As time goes on the materials will soften up and you end up with a pillowy experience that feels just a bit soft.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29106, 329, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The overall comfort of the Soldier 11 is definitely an improvement over the Soldier 10 and feels pretty nice.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29107, 329, 293, 100.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'The rubber is pretty hard, so outdoor play should be okay.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29108, 329, 293, 3.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'Doesn''t feel as wide as previous Soldier Models.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29109, 329, 293, 3.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'Go true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29110, 329, 522, 3.00, '2017-12-27', 'size', 'True to size for everyone.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29111, 330, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Overall the shoe is very similar to the KD 9. I like the firmer cushioning, the soft and flexible upper, but the support could be better.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29112, 330, 44, 8.60, '2017-12-27', 'expert_overall', 'The KD10 is a great shoe overall but there are some downfalls like the lacking of lateral support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29113, 330, 293, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'I like the shoe a lot! If you are not looking to do heavy lateral cuts or be really shifty then this is a great shoe! Very comfortable fit and great cushion make these perfect when you want to give your legs some extra comfort.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29114, 330, 176, 8.40, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Compared to the KD9, the Zoom is toned down, for good and bad. The materials are definitely improved. The looks  lets face it, this is a beautiful shoe. But the traction slid a little and the overall playability seemed a step back from the KD9.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29115, 330, 85, 8.40, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The KD10 just misses being a great shoe due to minor flaws in construction and traction  but they dont deter it from being a good performance shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29116, 330, 615, 8.30, '2017-12-27', 'expert_overall', 'Overall, the KD10 is a decent shoe, it just not as good as the KD9.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29117, 330, 6, 8.10, '2017-12-27', 'expert_overall', 'Overall, this is a good shoe. Unfortunately, traction and support keep it from being great.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29118, 330, 32, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike KD 9 was an amazing shoe. The Nike KD 10 was almost an amazing shoe. It looks amazing, but it suffered in a few areas due to the bold new design.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29119, 330, 486, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Overall the KD 10 performs solid in all categories. There is nothing phenomenal but on the flip side there is also nothing bad.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29120, 330, 497, 7.80, '2022-01-13', 'user_overall', 'The Nike KD10 was definitely not my favourite shoe, but it definitely wasnt the worst. It is mostly suitable for forwards. The traction was decent on a clean court, but on dust, it was very sloppy. The cushion was okay, but it didnt have all too much court feel. I also found the shoe a little stiff. The support was very sloppy tho, and my foot would always slide out the footbed. Ankle support wasnt great either. The materials were okay and a little breathable, but the laces were inconvenient.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29121, 330, 760, 8.40, '2023-01-30', 'user_overall', 'I think the cushioning is very good but has little durability because it broke very easy, and this didnt only happened to me, my friends happened too.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29122, 330, 761, 7.40, '2023-08-08', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29123, 330, 651, 9.00, '2021-11-29', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29124, 330, 495, 9.00, '2022-01-10', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29125, 330, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Overall, traction is pretty solid.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29126, 330, 44, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'traction', 'I absolutely love the traction!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29127, 330, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Nothing incredible or groundbreaking but traction is good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29128, 330, 176, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'I never experienced any straight slipping in moves or game play, but traction didn''t bite the way I like it.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29129, 330, 85, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'While the outsole design did provide multi-directional coverage, the grooves picked up dust  especially on the forefoot and heel points');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29130, 330, 615, 8.00, '2017-12-27', 'traction', 'The traction is inconsistent, works well on clean courts, but on dusty courts, you will need to wipe a lot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29131, 330, 6, 7.50, '2017-12-27', 'traction', 'The traction is just okay. On dusty courts, I was sliding a lot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29132, 330, 32, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction on both of my KD 10s just didnt work out for me.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29133, 330, 486, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction is solid.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29134, 330, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Cushioning is a bit more firm compared to the KD9, but I like the more responsive setup.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29135, 330, 44, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'cushion', 'Springy is the word that comes to mind.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29136, 330, 293, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Good impact protection, super bouncy, great heel to toe transition but you lose a little court feel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29137, 330, 176, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'This is the way Nike Zoom should feel, all day, every day.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29138, 330, 85, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Full-length Articulated Max Zoom Air. The ride was responsive without taking away from court feel but there is also plenty of impact protection');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29139, 330, 615, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'cushion', 'This time the cushioning is a bit firmer compared to the KD9.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29140, 330, 6, 8.50, '2017-12-27', 'cushion', 'Full-length Zoom - but it doesn''t feel anything like the KD9. This time the cushion is firmer and more responsive.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29141, 330, 32, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The cushion offers the best impact protection Nike currently has available.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29142, 330, 486, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Max cushioning of full length zoom, but I prefer more court feel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29143, 330, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Flyknit upper is super soft and flexible');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29144, 330, 44, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'materials', 'The reinforced FlyKnit is very comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29145, 330, 293, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Flyknit materials are very premium, top notch!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29146, 330, 176, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Soft, pliable, comfy, and form-fitting, the upper of the KD is what the future of Flyknit in basketball should be.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29147, 330, 85, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Flyknit materials are everything when done correctly and here, from heel to forefoot, its Flyknit errrry-thang!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29148, 330, 615, 8.00, '2017-12-27', 'materials', 'Materials work, but I liked the KD9 materials much better.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29149, 330, 6, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'materials', 'The full FlyKnit upper feels amazing.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29150, 330, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'I love the materials that were used on the Nike KD 10, I just dont love how they performed.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29151, 330, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Lockdown is really good but can be a little painful.  On hard cuts, I felt the shoe roll over a little bit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29152, 330, 44, 7.00, '2017-12-27', 'support', 'The upper material is too soft and doesn''t provide enough lateral support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29153, 330, 293, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Front to back was okay, but lateral support isn''t great');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29154, 330, 176, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'There are no serious structures to prevent rollover, just a good fit, wide base, and solid heel counter.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29155, 330, 85, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'I had an issue with the shoe: one of my lace loops ripped. Apart from that, the containment was decent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29156, 330, 6, 7.00, '2017-12-27', 'support', 'This is probably the most disappointing aspect of the shoe. Great heel support, but the FlyKnit in the forefoot doesn''t offer a lot of containment.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29157, 330, 32, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Despite the base of the shoe being a solid platform, it just wasnt enough to say these are cutting it in the support department.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29158, 330, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Way easier to put the shoe on compared to the KD 9.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29159, 330, 44, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'fit', 'The foot is held in nicely.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29160, 330, 176, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The fit of the shoe is almost perfect.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29161, 330, 85, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The fit of the shoe is fine but intense lateral cuts and heavy rotations on-court may cause some instabilities.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29162, 330, 615, 8.00, '2017-12-27', 'fit', 'If you pull the laces really tight, the fit is pretty good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29163, 330, 6, 8.50, '2017-12-27', 'fit', 'The Flyknit upper provides a nice 1:1 fit and the KD10 is much easier to put on compared to the KD9.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29164, 330, 32, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Heel lockdown was great but the midfoot lockdown was atrocious.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29165, 330, 486, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Flyknit is really soft but the fit is a little less snug than the KD9 elite.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29166, 330, 293, 0.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'Outdoor use is not recommended at all.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29167, 330, 293, 4.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'I would suggest going down half a size');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29168, 330, 6, 4.00, '2017-12-27', 'size', 'They run slightly long.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29169, 330, 486, 4.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'I would recommend to go half a size down.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29170, 331, 32, 9.20, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Is the Curry 3ZER0 leaps and bounds better than the Curry 3? No. However, the cushion feels more refined and offers a better balance between stability and protection.  If youre a guard or a shooter and plan on trying out the Curry 3ZER0 I think youll be pleasantly surprised.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29171, 331, 522, 8.60, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Out of the three Curry models released this year, Id put the Low first, the 3Zero slightly behind at second and then the Mid. The Curry 3 Zero is a more minimal shoe that doesn''t rely on bells and whistles or tech mumbo-jumbo, which I personally enjoy.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29172, 331, 6, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'For a $120 this is not a bad shoe! Really good on-court performer and I like the fit much better compared to the original Curry 3. I just wish they hadn''t downgraded the material from Threadborne to Mesh.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29173, 331, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The SC 3Zero is a solid second line shoe. Overall, I wasn''t a big fan of the new cushioning setup and the inconsistent traction. However, I did like the improved ankle support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29174, 331, 293, 7.80, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Just like the Curry 3, nothing special. I wasn''t happy with the fit and the traction. Let''s hope for an improved Curry 4.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29175, 331, 439, 8.60, '2023-04-24', 'user_overall', 'These shoes I got were previously owned,but the lock down and outrigger was something else as you never have to worry about rolling your ankle while playing basketball in them.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29176, 331, 569, 8.60, '2022-08-14', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29177, 331, 762, 8.00, '2023-12-22', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29178, 331, 763, 8.60, '2022-06-20', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29179, 331, 32, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Herringbone and solid rubber  the things that make for some beastly traction no matter the court condition.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29180, 331, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Great on clean floors but will require wiping when dusty.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29181, 331, 6, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Traction is very good on clean or dusty courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29182, 331, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'On clean courts you are ready to go, on mildly dusty courts you will need to wipe from time to time.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29183, 331, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Traction on clean courts is really good, but the shoe is a real dust magnet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29184, 331, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'If you wanted a cushion that balances stability and comfort then this is the setup for you.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29185, 331, 522, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Overall there is no real difference in cushioning so if you didnt like the cushioning on the 2.5 or 3, you wont like these either.  Personally, I find these work well for me and my game but to each their own.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29186, 331, 6, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Micro-G cushion is a lot more forgiving than the firmer Curry 3 Charged cushioning.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29187, 331, 31, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The cushioning setup is a little stiffer than the original Curry 3. I personally wasn''t a fan and would have liked a little more bounce.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29188, 331, 293, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The cushioning is very, very stiff. The insole is nice, impact protection is decent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29189, 331, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'This setup is very durable and worked just fine on-court. However, some break-in time is required.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29190, 331, 522, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Sacrifices come in the form of the materials. Reinforced mesh is used instead of Threadborne and plastic instead of carbon fiber for the meta wing and midfoot shank.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29191, 331, 6, 7.50, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Materials are pretty basic.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29192, 331, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Lightweight, flexible and breathable materials.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29193, 331, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'After a few days, the materials become soft and comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29194, 331, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'The shoes tooling sits wide and stable  built in outrigger included.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29195, 331, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Lockdown is perfectly fine and stability is very good as is with a contoured forefoot and flat outsole.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29196, 331, 6, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'The lockdown is crazy good thanks to the adjustable heel sleeve.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29197, 331, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'The adjustable heel provides great ankle support and works great for ankle brace wearers.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29198, 331, 293, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Very good lockdown, strong upper materials, good support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29199, 331, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Comfortable fit, even when wearing an ankle brace.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29200, 331, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Less puffy padding makes the Curry 3Zero less bulky than the Curry 3.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29201, 331, 6, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The fit is a huge improvement over the Curry 3.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29202, 331, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Not as comfortable as the original Curry 3. They feel really stiff in the beginning but get more comfortable after a while.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29203, 331, 293, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'There is so much toe room that I had to put in an additional 4mm insole.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29204, 331, 6, 50.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'The rubber is pretty hard, so outdoor use should be okay.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29205, 331, 293, 50.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'Outdoor use should be okay.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29206, 331, 6, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'The run slightly more narrow than the Curry 3.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29207, 331, 293, 3.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'Regular width, but lots of toe room.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29208, 331, 6, 4.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'Go down half a size, or stay true to size if you have a wide foot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29209, 331, 293, 4.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'Go down half a size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29210, 332, 32, 8.60, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The ANTA KT Outdoor 2 Low is a very good hoop shoe that offers a little bit of everything  court feel, semi-plush cushioning, durable traction that works on a variety of surfaces, and materials that are very much in line with what other brands are offering.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29211, 332, 739, 8.30, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The Anta KT Outdoor 2 Low is a solid shoe. It''s very light, has good impact protection and superb traction. I highly recommend this shoe for hoopers who love to play in both indoor and outdoor courts.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29212, 332, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'I was really impressed with this shoes, especially at $80! This will be my go-to outdoor shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29213, 332, 764, 8.20, '2023-04-08', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29214, 332, 30, 8.40, '2024-12-15', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29215, 332, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'This is an outdoor specific outsole that works wonders indoors and outdoors.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29216, 332, 739, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'I think the traction is the best feature of this shoe. Works great indoors and outdoors.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29217, 332, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'On a clean court, traction is great. Unfortunately, they pick up dust very fast.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29218, 332, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Not only is the cushion comfortable but it does a good job of absorbing impact.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29219, 332, 739, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Nice cushioning in the heel, but I wished there was more in the forefoot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29220, 332, 293, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The cushion is very soft and bouncy with great impact protection.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29221, 332, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Mesh and synthetics are used on the ANTA KT Outdoor 2 Low which is a significant improvement over the entirely fuse-based KT Outdoor 1.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29222, 332, 739, 7.50, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Mesh can be found in the forefoot and synthetic leather on the heel and ankle area. Not innovative at all - but gets the job done!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29223, 332, 293, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Materials are soft, but they feel really cheap.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29224, 332, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Overall support in the KT Outdoor 2 Low is solid.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29225, 332, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'The wide base offers great lateral stability.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29226, 332, 32, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'There is a small amount of heel slip at times.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29227, 332, 739, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'fit', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29228, 332, 293, 100.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'For outdoor use it''s very, very good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29229, 332, 293, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'Slightly narrow.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29230, 332, 293, 4.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'They run a touch long.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29231, 333, 486, 9.30, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'I think this is a very good shoe. Great traction, nice materials and an outstanding fit (for narrow feet). This is a BIG upgrade over the original Kobe AD');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29232, 333, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The NXT version of the Kobe A.D. has much more in common with the Kobe 11 than with the ori');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29233, 333, 522, 8.80, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'It is just a well-rounded performer with great traction, fun cushioning, excellent fit and stability and decent containment. These edge out the Curry 3 Low for my favorite of 2017.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29234, 333, 293, 8.80, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'For $200 this shoe is a no-go. Disregarding the price, the Kobe AD NXT is a really good performer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29235, 333, 649, 8.80, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The Kobe AD NXT has some exciting high points and I truly enjoyed playing in these thanks to the fantastic upper comfort. Unfortunately, at $200 this is the most expensive basketball shoe model in the 2017 Nike lineup. There are far better values out there.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29236, 333, 701, 8.30, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29237, 333, 651, 9.00, '2022-03-30', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29238, 333, 746, 9.60, '2022-07-04', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29239, 333, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'I really enjoyed the traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29240, 333, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction had no issues on any surface no matter the condition.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29241, 333, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'I had no issues at all with the NXT traction, well done Nike!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29242, 333, 293, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Traction bites really hard on clean courts. On dusty courts, you will need to wipe a lot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29243, 333, 649, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'From game one, the Kobe A.D. NXTs traction was top-notch.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29244, 333, 701, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'I was very happy with the traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29245, 333, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Lunarlon midsole with a Nike Zoom unit in the heel - one of my favorite setups.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29246, 333, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The large volume heel Zoom Air unit coupled with a Lunarlon midsole works very well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29247, 333, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'I could feel the heel Zoom and Lunarlon from the get-go. Well done Nike!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29248, 333, 293, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Heel Zoom unit provides you with decent impact protection.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29249, 333, 649, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The Zoom bag provided plenty of impact protection, but Lunarlon quickly lost a lot of its initial cushioning.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29250, 333, 701, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'I thought the cushioning setup was pretty good on these. A great balance between cushioning and court feel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29251, 333, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'A mixture of mesh and knit provides the best Nike has to offer.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29252, 333, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The shoe is made out of a mesh textile build that is very breathable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29253, 333, 522, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'No issues here but for $200 youd think youd get all Flyknit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29254, 333, 293, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The materials are very nice and super soft from the get-go.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29255, 333, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'You sit low to the ground so stability is great while the overall containment (from the fit) is wonderful.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29256, 333, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Overall, I really liked the mobility of wearing a low without any fear or turning my ankle.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29257, 333, 293, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Support is very good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29258, 333, 649, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Great heel lockdown and two subtle outriggers help the shoe to excel in this area.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29259, 333, 486, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'I don''t think there is another shoe that will fit as great as this one.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29260, 333, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'For those that enjoy that really snug feeling on-foot then youll likely enjoy the hell out of these.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29261, 333, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'I had no movement side to side and zero heel slip. I really enjoyed the one to one fit with the NXT.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29262, 333, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The new lacing system is a no-go. You can''t really get it to securely lock down your forefoot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29263, 333, 649, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The new lacing system not only sounds great on paper but also actually works. The feel of the NXTs upper is second to none. I wasnt able to achieve a fit quite as snug as with traditional lacing systems, but there was still enough support that the tradeoff was well worth it in terms of comfort.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29264, 333, 701, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'I had a little heel slippage, the lockdown was fine and the shoes were really comfortable.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29265, 333, 293, 0.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'Outdoor use is not recommended.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29266, 333, 522, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'Wide footers can go up half a size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29267, 333, 293, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'The fit is rather narrow similar to other Kobe models.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29268, 333, 701, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'They are a little narrow.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29269, 333, 522, 3.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'These fit true to size lengthwise.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29270, 333, 293, 4.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'Go down half a size if you have narrow feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29271, 333, 701, 3.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'They''re true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29272, 334, 31, 9.50, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'At $110 these are by far the best value performance basketball shoes available right now.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29273, 334, 755, 8.80, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The Nike PG 1 features a consistent traction experience that holds up on a wide variety of court conditions as well as a decent cushion setup that favors quick, low to the ground players. At $110, its worth a shot right?');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29274, 334, 486, 8.70, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Overall I thought that shoe performed great! It''s my go-to shoe right now and I will be hooping in them for a while!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29275, 334, 6, 8.60, '2017-12-27', 'expert_overall', 'For $110, I can absolutely recommend these shoes.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29276, 334, 649, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The PG1 performs on a level that far exceeds its relatively low price tag.  Its cushioning and stability are top-notch, making it my favorite Nike of the season at any price.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29277, 334, 32, 8.40, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'I will say that the Nike PG1 is very good if youre looking for a shoe that feels like an extension of your foot without breaking the bank.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29278, 334, 85, 8.40, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The PG1 is a wonderful shoe to play in, as long as you dont have wide feet and you can get your foot into the shoe. For a first signature model and its $110 price point, I think the shoe is fantastic.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29279, 334, 293, 8.40, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'I really like to play in the Nike PG1. Cushion and fit are nice and the traction gets good after breaking them in.  At $110 they are a real steal!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29280, 334, 701, 8.30, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'For only $110 it  is a very, very good performance basketball sneaker.  You won''t worry about sliding around, slipping on the floor, or the lockdown of the shoe. A');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29281, 334, 522, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'Overall, the PG1 is a great start to a new signature shoe, far better than the Kyrie 1 in my opinion. Cushioning isnt the best or very fun but it works fine while  the rest of the shoe performs very well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29282, 334, 560, 10.00, '2023-12-22', 'user_overall', 'God, I miss these shoes! I wore them for 5 years, 3 on court and then 2 as normal sneakers. The flywire always felt tight and the shoe fit like a glove. They were rigid when needed, and flexed when I was on my toes. The materials used in the midsole and sole should be the gold standard for all shoes. I hope they come back as a reissue. Truly my perfect shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29283, 334, 609, 9.70, '2024-07-02', 'user_overall', 'How it only 110$ i didn''t expect much the first time i tried it. It was amazing! It was super responsive the cushioning was super average but soft the traction was great but not recommended for outdoor users the fit was amazing the support was good this shoe is flawless the best budget shoe in 2017 i love wearing it.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29284, 334, 439, 9.00, '2023-04-24', 'user_overall', 'The best I have ever played with,My brother first got it from a thrift store and used It for 2 years and then gave it to my cousin for 2 years.Now I have used it for 2 years and the shoe still has top tier traction.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29285, 334, 496, 8.70, '2022-10-11', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29286, 334, 765, 9.00, '2023-04-11', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29287, 334, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'These shoes grip to the floor really well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29288, 334, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'It isnt quite elite, but the PG 1s traction is just below that top tier thanks to its consistent performance on multiple surfaces.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29289, 334, 486, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction of the PG1 held it''s own and the translucent rubber sole didn''t cause me any problems.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29290, 334, 6, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'traction', 'The traction bites really hard and I didn''t have to wipe a lot.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29291, 334, 649, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'From my first run in the PG1, I had secure footing and was making confident movements with minimal swiping.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29292, 334, 32, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The good news is that the pattern here really helps the rubber compound out and dust doesnt stick to the pattern much.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29293, 334, 85, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The solid rubber outsole and traction worked above average');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29294, 334, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'I was very disappointed at first, but after a while they broke in and got really good. Dust is a problem.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29295, 334, 701, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction is the best aspect of the shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29296, 334, 522, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'Traction on the PG1 is on par with the Mamba Instinct, Kobe AD which is pretty damn good. Well done Nike!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29297, 334, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The cushioning of the forefoot zoom is by far my favorite part of this shoe because it is responsive like hell.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29298, 334, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Can you find better value at $110? Probably, but for a signature model, it doesnt get much better than this.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29299, 334, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Forefoot zoom might be not enough cushion for some. But for me, this is a healthy balance between Kyrie 3 and Lebron 14.  I really can''t ask for much more!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29300, 334, 6, 8.00, '2017-12-27', 'cushion', 'I like the Zoom unit in the forefoot. Gives you a good blend of responsiveness and impact protection.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29301, 334, 649, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The PG1 doesnt introduce any groundbreaking cushioning, but it incorporates the best use of standard Zoom Air in recent memory.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29302, 334, 32, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Some may feel the setup is a bit lackluster if theyre expecting an abundant amount of cushion, but if you are more into court feel then this will prove to be a worthy setup.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29303, 334, 85, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Forefoot Zoom, soft Phylon midsole, responsive court feel  that combination is definitely a setup worth taking a second look at.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29304, 334, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'A little bit of cushion in the front, the heel is pretty much dead.  Very responsive feel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29305, 334, 701, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Impact protection is just not excellent.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29306, 334, 522, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'At $110, I didnt expect much in terms of Zoom and it feels decent overall but feels just like a budget Nike shoe set up to me.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29307, 334, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The materials are really nice and feel soft and flexible.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29308, 334, 755, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The inner-bootie construction uses an extremely soft mesh/neoprene material that just feels too luxurious to be valued at $110.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29309, 334, 6, 8.00, '2017-12-27', 'materials', 'Materials are on the budget side but get the job done');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29310, 334, 32, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'This is one of the best material options weve had from Nike Basketball in a long time.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29311, 334, 85, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The materials here are absolutely the star of the show.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29312, 334, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'For a budget model the materials are really good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29313, 334, 522, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'Its a nice blend of old and new school materials that really gives the feel of a much more expensive shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29314, 334, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Support and lockdown are excellent. The forefoot strap really locks your feet in.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29315, 334, 755, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29316, 334, 6, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'support', 'The strap provides great forefoot lockdown and there was zero heel slippage.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29317, 334, 649, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Lockdown was secure in all directions. Stability inspired confidence yet still allowed for optimal range of motion.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29318, 334, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Gives you the feeling that youre not just wearing a shoe, but that the shoe is part of you.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29319, 334, 85, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Wonderful lockdown, solid traction, responsive ride  Id say its pretty supportive, especially for a first signature model that is a low-top.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29320, 334, 293, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'Heel feels a bit loose because of the bootie design.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29321, 334, 701, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'The lockdown is really good thanks to the forefoot strap.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29322, 334, 522, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'support', 'No issues with the support at all. Stability is fantastic on the PG1 thanks to a large forefoot outrigger and flat outsole.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29323, 334, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'A little snug and a little tight but the fit felt really nice.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29324, 334, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The PG 1 provides a close one-to-one fit that stays with your foot during every cut, drive, jab and stop.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29325, 334, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'The overall fit was the best feature of this shoe. After a break in period the feel crazy good!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29326, 334, 6, 9.00, '2017-12-27', 'fit', 'The one-bootie construction was a nice fit for my feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29327, 334, 649, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'I ultimately found the fit to be great. But the method in which its achieved isnt ideal from an ease-of-use or comfort standpoint.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29328, 334, 32, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Lockdown is incredible. The midfoot feels perfectly secure and there are only four lace loops.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29329, 334, 85, 7.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Even 1/2 size up, the PG1 required some break-in time due to the snugness.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29330, 334, 293, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'Fit is pretty good.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29331, 334, 522, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'fit', 'To me, the fit is the highlight of the shoe.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29332, 334, 293, 0.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'The rubber is really soft so outdoor use is not recommended');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29333, 334, 522, 0.00, '2017-01-01', 'outdoor', 'Forefoot upper might get beat up outdoors since it is mesh.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29334, 334, 486, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'Wide footers: you need to try them on first!');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29335, 334, 6, 2.00, '2017-12-27', 'width', 'The PG1 runs fairly narrow.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29336, 334, 293, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'Pretty snug, you could go half a size up if you have wide feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29337, 334, 701, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'The fit is really narrow.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29338, 334, 522, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'width', 'The thick sockliner probably contributes to the tighter than normal fit of the PG1.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29339, 334, 6, 3.00, '2017-12-27', 'size', 'Runs true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29340, 334, 293, 3.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'Runs true to size.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29341, 334, 522, 2.00, '2017-01-01', 'size', 'I opted for half size up and all was better though');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29342, 335, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'When it comes to performance the KD9 Elite is very similar to the original KD9. The most notable difference is the strong lacing cables which slightly enhance support and lockdown. However, this new lacing setup also makes the shoe even narrower which led to some pain on the side of my feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29343, 335, 486, 8.80, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'A great shoe with slight improvements over the original KD9. The upper material is softer and more comfortable and the new lacing system provides more lockdown and support.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29344, 335, 293, 8.50, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'It''s a very specific shoe. Great if you have narrow feet and you are looking for a shoe with a lot of cushion and impact protection. If you are a shifty guard who does a lot of crossovers and cuts then the lacking support of the upper and the slightly unstable platform are not ideal. Not recommended if you have wide feet.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29345, 335, 755, 7.80, '2017-01-01', 'expert_overall', 'The traction, cushion, and materials all bring out the best of Nikes technology, unfortunately, the KD 9 Elite doesn''t perform as well when it comes to support and fit.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29346, 335, 766, 10.00, '2025-04-18', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29347, 335, 462, 9.60, '2022-05-31', 'user_overall', NULL);
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29348, 335, 31, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The traction is really solid.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29349, 335, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The honeycomb pattern is the same as in the KD9 and works very well.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29350, 335, 293, 8.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'On clean courts, it''s really nice, but on dusty courts, you are screwed.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29351, 335, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'traction', 'The overall traction experience is pretty consistent and has you covered in all directions.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29352, 335, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'A springy light cushioning setup. A lot of impact protection but I would have preferred more court feel.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29353, 335, 486, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Full length-zoom remains unchanged.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29354, 335, 293, 10.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'The full-length Nike Zoom cushioning is close to an ideal cushion.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29355, 335, 755, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'cushion', 'Unchanged from the Original KD 9, and we''re perfectly okay with that.');
INSERT INTO public."Review" VALUES (29356, 335, 31, 9.00, '2017-01-01', 'materials', 'The materials are lightweight, flexible and wrap around your feet really nicely.');
